doEntry.name: doEntry
doEntry.description: An entry containing all of the action (do) commands and the slot and item index.

doSlotIndex.name: doSlotIndex
doSlotIndex.description: The index of the slot containing the item for which an action is desired. The valid range is 1 through the value slotNumber.

doItemIndex.name: doItemIndex
doItemIndex.description: The item number on the indexed slot for which an action is desired. The valid range is 1 through the value slotItems in the slotTable when indexed by a value equal to doSlotIndex.

doDial.name: doDial
doDial.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can dial a call. Writing any value will cause a call to be placed when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doHangUp.name: doHangUp
doHangUp.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can terminate a call. Writing any value will cause the call to be terminated when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doAnswer.name: doAnswer
doAnswer.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can answer a call. Writing any value will cause the call to be answered when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doExtendBW.name: doExtendBW
doExtendBW.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can extend bandwidth. Writing any value will cause bandwidth to be extended when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doContractBW.name: doContractBW
doContractBW.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can contract bandwidth. Writing any value will cause bandwidth to be contracted when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doBegEndRemoteLB.name: doBegEndRemoteLB
doBegEndRemoteLB.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can enter or exit remote loopback. Writing any value will cause the current remote loopback state to be toggled when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doBegEndBERT.name: doBegEndBERT
doBegEndBERT.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can enter or exit BERT test mode. Writing any value will cause the current BERT test state to be toggled when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

doResynchronize.name: doResynchronize
doResynchronize.description: When read returns valid if the indexed slot/item can issue a resynchronize command. Writing any value will cause a resynchronize command to be issued when valid, otherwise the write is ignored.

hostStatusTable.name: hostStatusTable
hostStatusTable.description: A table of host port status entries. A host port status entry potentialy exists for every slot/item. Host port status entries are only meaningful for slot/items that reference a host port. When indexed by other slot/items NO SUCH NAME will be returned.

hostStatusEntry.name: hostStatusEntry
hostStatusEntry.description: An entry containing the host port status of the indexed slot/item.

hostStatusSlotIndex.name: hostStatusSlotIndex
hostStatusSlotIndex.description: A unique value for each slot. The slot identified by a particular value of this index is the same slot as identified by the same value of slotIndex.

hostStatusItemIndex.name: hostStatusItemIndex
hostStatusItemIndex.description: Index to each item defined for each slot. Since entries in this table are only valid for host ports an item number is a port number within the indexed slot.

hostStatusLocalName.name: hostStatusLocalName
hostStatusLocalName.description: The name from the current call profile of the indexed host slot and port.

hostStatusDialNum.name: hostStatusDialNum
hostStatusDialNum.description: The phone number from the current call profile of the indexed host slot and port.

hostStatusCallType.name: hostStatusCallType
hostStatusCallType.description: The type of call from the current call profile of the indexed host slot and port.

hostStatusCallMgm.name: hostStatusCallMgm
hostStatusCallMgm.description: The call management protocol from the current call profile for the indexed host slot and port. Call management is only meaningful for calls using an inverse multiplexing protocol.

hostStatusDataSvc.name: hostStatusDataSvc
hostStatusDataSvc.description: The type of service from the current call profile for the indexed host slot and port.

hostStatusCallState.name: hostStatusCallState
hostStatusCallState.description: Shows the current state of the current call for the indexed host slot and port. The returned value will indicates the same state displayed in a call status window for the port.

hostStatusRemName.name: hostStatusRemName
hostStatusRemName.description: The value displayed on the 4th line of the call status menu. When the hostStatusCallType is aim( 1 ) this value is the name of the host port on the far end of a connection, or the far-end system name if the host port has not been named. An empty string is returned when there is no call active or when aim( 1 ) is not being used.

hostStatusChannels.name: hostStatusChannels
hostStatusChannels.description: The number of channels in use by the call as displayed on the third line of the call status menu for the indexed slot and port.

hostStatusDuration.name: hostStatusDuration
hostStatusDuration.description: The duration of the call associated with the indexed host slot and port, measured in seconds.

consoleNumber.name: consoleNumber
consoleNumber.description: The number of consoles supported by this device.

consoleEntry.name: consoleEntry
consoleEntry.description: An entry containing objects that describe the indexed console port.

consoleIndex.name: consoleIndex
consoleIndex.description: A unique value for each console. It's value ranges between 1 and the value consoleNumber. This is the index into the console table to identify a particular console.

consoleIf.name: consoleIf
consoleIf.description: The interface number associated with the indexed console. This number can be used to index into the interface (and other) tables to obtain detailed console status.

consoleType.name: consoleType
consoleType.description: The type of console in the indexed entry. When no console is plugged into a console port the value inactive(5) is returned. The value remote(6) indicates a console initiated via remote management or TELNET session.

consoleSecurity.name: consoleSecurity
consoleSecurity.description: The security profile, in the range of 1 through the number of profiles supported by the unit, of the indexed console. The default security profile is profile number 1. Note: This attribute is supported on non-TNT platforms only.

consoleSpecific.name: consoleSpecific
consoleSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the console port. Contains the object identifier { 0 0 } if there is no console specific information for the indexed console.

sysAbsoluteStartupTime.name: sysAbsoluteStartupTime
sysAbsoluteStartupTime.description: The time system startup up in seconds since January 1, 1990. This value in concert with 'sysSecsSinceStartup' below can be used to compute the current time in seconds since 1/1/90.

sysSecsSinceStartup.name: sysSecsSinceStartup
sysSecsSinceStartup.description: The number of seconds since system startup.

sysMibVersionNum.name: sysMibVersionNum
sysMibVersionNum.description: Version number of this private MIB. Versions numbers start at 1 and increment by 1 for every major revision. Major revisions are additions/deletions to this MIB.

sysMibMinorRevNum.name: sysMibMinorRevNum
sysMibMinorRevNum.description: Value represents the minor revision number of this MIB. Minor revision numbers start at 0 and increment by 1 for each revision. Minor revisions are textual or comment changes.

sysConfigTftpCmd.name: sysConfigTftpCmd
sysConfigTftpCmd.description: This variable instructs the system to perform the specified tftp operation. Note: loadCode( 6 ) is not supported on TNT platform.

sysConfigTftpStatus.name: sysConfigTftpStatus
sysConfigTftpStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of a save or restore operation through tftp.

sysConfigTftpHostAddr.name: sysConfigTftpHostAddr
sysConfigTftpHostAddr.description: This variable indicates the host address where the configuration file is saved to or restored from through tftp.

sysConfigTftpFilename.name: sysConfigTftpFilename
sysConfigTftpFilename.description: This variable indicates the file name of the configuration file to save to or restore from a SNMP host through tftp.

sysConfigTftpPort.name: sysConfigTftpPort
sysConfigTftpPort.description: This variable indicates the port # to use when starting a TSAVE TRESTORE command. Normally this would be port 69, but we need to allow the Java Console to override this in case the Console workstation has a TFTP server already running.

sysConfigTftpParameter.name: sysConfigTftpParameter
sysConfigTftpParameter.description: This variable indicates the list of profiles to be included or excluded during the save operation through tftp. The snmp agent will modify the set string to an uppercase space-separated new string and return the changed value. This is to clarify the case insensitive profile naming.

sysConfigRadiusCmd.name: sysConfigRadiusCmd
sysConfigRadiusCmd.description: This variable instructs the system to re-read its RADIUS configuration. This variable will return a general error if RADIUS is not configured or if sysConfigRadiusStatus has a value of processing(2).

sysConfigRadiusStatus.name: sysConfigRadiusStatus
sysConfigRadiusStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the last RADIUS configuration retrieval. This includes the boot time retrieval.

sysAbsoluteCurrentTime.name: sysAbsoluteCurrentTime
sysAbsoluteCurrentTime.description: The current system time in seconds since January 1, 1990. Changing this value may result in a change of sysAbsoluteStartupTime and not of sysSecsSinceStartup. The following relationship holds: sysAbsoluteCurrentTime - sysAbsoluteStartupTime = sysSecsSinceStartup.

sysReset.name: sysReset
sysReset.description: The reset takes effect after 1 minute.

sysLoadName.name: sysLoadName
sysLoadName.description: The name of the load which is currently running.

sysAuthPreference.name: sysAuthPreference
sysAuthPreference.description: An incoming call can be authenticated using a local profile or one from an authentication server such as RADIUS or TACACS. local-first means authenticate from a local profile first, and if that fails, try the authentication server. remote-first means get a profile from the authentication server and authenticate from that and if that fails, try to authenticate from a local profile. remote-no is the same as remote-first except if the external authentication server NACKs the request, then the connection will be denied, i.e. no search of the local profiles will be made.

sysSPROMSerialNumber.name: sysSPROMSerialNumber
sysSPROMSerialNumber.description: The serial number as stored in the security PROM. The same value is also returned as part of sysName.

sysSPROMOptions1.name: sysSPROMOptions1
sysSPROMOptions1.description: The various bit positions are: (2 ** 0) - rs366Enabled (2 ** 1) - dChannelEnabled (2 ** 2) - autoDBAEnabled (2 ** 3) - bondingEnabled (2 ** 4) - aimEnabled (2 ** 5) - v25bisEnabled (2 ** 6) - x21Enabled (2 ** 7) - switchedEnabled (2 ** 8) - mrateEnabled (2 ** 9) - pbxEnabled (2 ** 10) - pcbusEnabled (2 ** 11) - bridgingEnabled (2 ** 12) - pipeHxEnabled (2 ** 13) - frameRelayEnabled (2 ** 14) - maxLinkClientEnabled (2 ** 15) - dataCallEnabled (2 ** 16) - dualSlotT1Enabled (2 ** 17) - r2SignalingEnabled (2 ** 18) - domesticEnabled (2 ** 19) - modemTSDialoutEnabled (2 ** 20) - pipePxEnabled (2 ** 21) - firewallsEnabled (2 ** 22) - serialPortT1_CSU_Enabled (2 ** 23) - pipePotsEnabled (2 ** 24) - forceMultibandPlatformSimulationEnabled (2 ** 25) - k56SlotCardOnlyEnabled (2 ** 26) - networkManagementEnabled (2 ** 27) - advancedAgentEnabled (DEPRECATED) (2 ** 28) - phsSupportEnabled (2 ** 29) - selectoolsEnabled (2 ** 30) - routingProtocolsDisabled (2 ** 31) - tunnelProtocolsDisabled (DEPRECATED).

sysSPROMOptions2.name: sysSPROMOptions2
sysSPROMOptions2.description: The various bit positions are: (2 ** 0) - atmpEnabled (2 ** 1) - l2tpEnabled (2 ** 2) - pptpEnabled (2 ** 3) - l2fEnabled (2 ** 4) - ipinipEnabled (2 ** 5) - vRouterEnabled (2 ** 6) - aodiEnabled (2 ** 7) - maddModemEnabled (2 ** 8) - madd96DevicesEnabled (2 ** 9) - maddHdlcEnabled (2 ** 10) - v110Enabled (2 ** 11) - sdtnEnabled (2 ** 12) - restrictDSLTermEnabled (2 ** 13) - megamaxEnabled (2 ** 14) - maxtapEnabled (2 ** 15) - phs21Enabled (2 ** 16) - atmSvcEnabled (2 ** 17) - frVcEnabled (2 ** 18) - networkManagementVoipEnabled (2 ** 19) - networkManagementPlusEnabled (2 ** 20) - networkManagementPlusVoipEnabled

sysSPROMCountries1.name: sysSPROMCountries1
sysSPROMCountries1.description: The various bit positions are: (2 ** 0) - FranceIsdn (2 ** 1) - UKIsdn (2 ** 2) - BelgiumIsdn (2 ** 3) - JapanIsdn (2 ** 4) - AustraliaIsdn (2 ** 5) - GermanIsdn (2 ** 6) - UKDpnss (2 ** 7) - SwissIsdn (2 ** 8) - GloBandIsdn

sysLastRestartReason.name: sysLastRestartReason
sysLastRestartReason.description: The error code for the previous box restart. The error codes are identical to ones obtained via fatal-history from the debug monitor screen.

sysConfigChange.name: sysConfigChange
sysConfigChange.description: The name and security index (if available) of the user who changed the configuration.

fatalLogTable.name: fatalLogTable
fatalLogTable.description: A list of the most recent Fatal Log entries of the system as well as the included slot cards

fatalLogTableEntry.name: fatalLogTableEntry
fatalLogTableEntry.description: Definition of the row entries in the Fatal Log Table

fatalLogIndex.name: fatalLogIndex
fatalLogIndex.description: Dynamic index that reflects the index used in the Fatal LOG table, starting with the most oldest event.

fatalLogSlotIndex.name: fatalLogSlotIndex
fatalLogSlotIndex.description: An index into the slotTable This has the same value as slotIndex, it is set to 0 for systems with one logical slot card.

fatalLogSoftwareVerion.name: fatalLogSoftwareVerion
fatalLogSoftwareVerion.description: The version of the software running, when this entry was created by the system.

fatalLogUserprofile.name: fatalLogUserprofile
fatalLogUserprofile.description: The user responsible for reseting the card. This will be set to the empty string if unknown.

fatalLogLoadName.name: fatalLogLoadName
fatalLogLoadName.description: The name of the Load executing on the card, it gives a textual description of the software code that was running on the system when the entry was created.

fatalLogLocation.name: fatalLogLocation
fatalLogLocation.description: The IP address from which a manual system reset was triggered.

fatalLogReason.name: fatalLogReason
fatalLogReason.description: The reason for reset as reported by the system. For a more detailed description consult the user manual.

fatalLogAbsoluteTime.name: fatalLogAbsoluteTime
fatalLogAbsoluteTime.description: The time at which the system was reset.

sysConfigFlashCmd.name: sysConfigFlashCmd
sysConfigFlashCmd.description: This variable instructs the system to copy the stored code image from PCMCIA flash to internal flash or vice versa.

sysConfigFlashCopyStatus.name: sysConfigFlashCopyStatus
sysConfigFlashCopyStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of a flash image copy.

sysConfigInternalFlashImageVersion.name: sysConfigInternalFlashImageVersion
sysConfigInternalFlashImageVersion.description: The code version stored on the internal flash.

sysConfigPCMCIAFlashImageVersion.name: sysConfigPCMCIAFlashImageVersion
sysConfigPCMCIAFlashImageVersion.description: The code version stored on the PCMCIA flash.
